body:
bill & ted headcanons

- they both have super bad separation anxiety

- like, they can barley stand 3 days without seeing each other

- ted is the only person that bill allows to show him any physical affection

- and ted LOVES giving bill hugs with their height difference and adores the fact that he can just rest his chin on top of bill’s head

- wearing each other’s clothing is a common occurrence

- bill is a restless sleeper, so ted likes to cuddle him on school night sleepovers so they get at least 4-5 hours of sleep rather than the usual 1-2 hours 

- neither of them can cook for shit but ted can make a mean grilled cheese sandwich 

- though 9 times out 10 ten, the bread is usually burnt

- musicals are ted’s guilty pleasure

- bill is really good at drama class and has a high B in there

- the only reason why he doesn’t have a higher grade is due to the fact that he won’t shut up once he’s finished with a part in the script 

- both of them struggle with severe ADHD

- bill likes to sit in ted’s lap when they’re watching The Evil Dead in bill’s basement

- but bill always says, “i’m just cold, dude.” but he actually gets really freaked out when the monsters come on screen and believes wholeheartedly that ted will protect him (and he will)

- they share a birthday the month in-between the middle of their actual birthdays (bill’s in july, ted’s in september). their parents thought it’d be easier to celebrate since it saves money. plus, it isn’t like the boys are complaining about it

more will be added soon!
